<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870422-0122 </DOCNO><HL> Ford Is Recalling 405 Cars,Citing a Wheel Problem</HL><DD> 04/22/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> FAUTOS, AUTO PARTS (AUT) </IN><DATELINE> DEARBORN, Mich.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Ford Motor Co. said it is recalling 405 Ford Escort, Tempo and Mercury Lynx 1987-model cars to correct a condition that could cause the cars' wheels to separate from the vehicles.    The auto maker said wheel lug nuts mightn't hold. Ford also said it will inspect and, if necessary, replace the wheels and wheel studs.    Ford said 39 of the cars already may have been sold to retail customers. Most of the cars being recalled are in dealer stocks in the U.S. and Canada and certain export locations. The company said it doesn't know of any injuries or accidents resulting from the condition. </TEXT></DOC>